-- Japan Lawmakers Propose Troops on Island Disputed with China, Jiji Reports
-- B y   C h r i s   C o o p e r
-- 2010-09-27T22:34:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/japan-lawmakers-propose-troops-on-island-disputed-with-china-jiji-reports.html
A group of Japanese ruling party
lawmakers said the government should consider stationing troops
on the Senkaku Islands, which are disputed with China, Jiji
Press reported. Jin Matsubara, a Lower House member, was one of
12 lawmakers who made the proposal, the report said.  The lawmakers also said Japan should set up a fisheries
base on the islands, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
